# Modular Architecture

- Keep feature code in focused modules instead of growing large mixed files.
- Organize source by durable business function, not by roadmap phase or sprint.
- Treat roadmap phases as build order only; do not create phase-shaped source folders.
- Put shared domain types in capability-focused files under `src/shared` so Electron main, preload, and renderer agree on contracts.
- Put renderer feature state, components, and helpers under `src/renderer/features/<feature>`.
- Prefer stable feature folders such as `app-shell`, `workspaces`, `file-registry`, `safety`, `process-runner`, `agents`, `documents`, and `browser-automation`.
- Keep Electron IPC channels narrow and typed; expose only safe APIs through preload.
- Prefer adding/removing a feature by changing one feature folder plus its explicit shared contract.
- Avoid coupling UI components directly to Electron implementation details; call feature services or preload APIs.
